        "title": "refactor: extract normalization core package",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Extract shared normalization/coercion helpers into private workspace package `@openclaw/normalization-core` with built dist artifacts.\n- Rewrite core, UI, tooling, and package build imports to use the new package boundary while preserving existing `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*-runtime` public SDK subpaths.\n- Keep the new package name out of extension package-boundary aliases and emitted plugin SDK declarations, and wire UI/test resolvers for browser-safe imports.\n- Fix the slow PR CodeQL network-runtime lane by using a fast added-line PR scan and keeping full CodeQL for scheduled/manual runs.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/normalization-core/src src/plugins/sdk-alias.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/extension-package-project-boundaries.test.ts test/scripts/dev-tooling-safety.test.ts test/plugin-npm-release.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm --filter @openclaw/normalization-core build`\n- `pnpm build:plugin-sdk:dts && node --experimental-strip-types scripts/write-plugin-sdk-entry-dts.ts && rg -n \"@openclaw/normalization-core\" dist/plugin-sdk packages/plugin-sdk/dist || true`\n- `node scripts/build-all.mjs cliStartup`\n- `pnpm check:import-cycles`\n- `node scripts/check-package-dist-imports.mjs .`\n- `pnpm --dir ui build`\n- `pnpm --dir ui test src/ui/chat/slash-commands.browser-import.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/sessions/extensions/loader.test.ts src/agents/sessions/extensions/loader.native-js.test.ts src/plugins/plugin-sdk-native-resolver.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs --config test/vitest/vitest.agents-support.config.ts`\n- `pnpm build:ci-artifacts`\n- `pnpm lint --threads=8`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/ci-workflow-guards.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/check-workflows.mjs`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` clean\n- GitHub CI on head `963d893715b6526ff9e7806e2614c1a1f8013801` green after dependency-guard approval\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: shared number/string/record normalization helpers now live in private `@openclaw/normalization-core`; existing plugin SDK helper subpaths remain the public plugin API, and direct package imports stay internal.\nReal environment tested: local macOS checkout with repo Node/pnpm tooling plus GitHub CI for PR head `963d893715b6526ff9e7806e2614c1a1f8013801`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: the commands listed above, including normalization-core moved tests, plugin SDK alias/package-boundary tests, extension loader resolver tests, full agents-support shard, UI build/test, build artifacts, lint, workflow guard test, workflow lint, import-cycle checks, and branch autoreview.\nEvidence after fix: local commands passed; final autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings; GitHub CI reports no failing or pending checks on head `963d893715b6526ff9e7806e2614c1a1f8013801`; Dependency Guard authorized the current head SHA.\nObserved result after fix: package/runtime declarations no longer leak direct `@openclaw/normalization-core` imports through plugin SDK outputs, UI resolves the new package, plugin jiti/native loaders resolve internal package imports, CLI dist bundles the private package, import cycles remain clean, and the network CodeQL PR lane now completes via fast scan instead of hanging on full CodeQL startup.\nWhat was not tested: live gateway/provider flows; this is an internal package-boundary refactor with behavior-preserving moved tests.\n",
